"title": "4860: wind",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4860",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In Hebrew the same word can denote “breath”, “wind” or “spirit”. Scripture describes the powerful effect of wind, and uses the image figuratively to speak of God's power and presence in the world.</p>\n<h2>The origins of the wind</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:21-Exod14:22\">EXO 14:21–14:22</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:26\">PSA 78:26</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:13\">AMO 4:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:1\">GEN 8:1</a> <em>A wind caused the flood waters to recede</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:13-Exod10:14\">EXO 10:13–10:14</a> <em>An east wind brought the plague of locusts on Egypt</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:19\">EXO 10:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:31\">NUM 11:31</a> <em>A wind brought quail to feed the Israelites</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:25\">JOB 28:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:25\">PSA 107:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:7\">PSA 135:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps148:7-Ps148:8\">PSA 148:7–148:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:15\">ISA 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:13\">JER 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:13\">EZK 13:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:4\">JON 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:8\">JON 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>The effects of the wind</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:11\">1KI 19:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:26\">EZK 27:26</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:13-Acts27:15\">ACT 27:13–27:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:5-Gen41:6\">GEN 41:5–41:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:18-Job1:19\">JOB 1:18–1:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:9\">JOB 37:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:17-Job37:18\">JOB 37:17–37:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:2\">DAN 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:24\">MAT 14:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:55\">LUK 12:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:16-John6:18\">JHN 6:16–6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:4\">JAS 3:4</a></p>\n<h2>Wind used figuratively</h2>\n<h3>As an image of the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:8\">JHN 3:8</a></strong> <em>The Greek word for “Spirit” is the same as that for “wind”, allowing Jesus Christ to play on the double meaning of the word.</em></p>\n<h3>As an image of spiritual instability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:6\">JAS 1:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>As an image of destruction</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:15-Ps103:16\">PSA 103:15–103:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:24-Matt7:27\">MAT 7:24–7:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:17-Job21:18\">JOB 21:17–21:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:4\">PSA 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps48:7\">PSA 48:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:13\">ISA 17:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:2\">ISA 32:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:11-Jer4:12\">JER 4:11–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:22\">JER 22:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:12\">EZK 19:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:34-Dan2:35\">DAN 2:34–2:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:7\">HOS 8:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:14\">AMO 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:9\">HAB 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:14\">EPH 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:12\">JUD 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:12-Rev6:13\">REV 6:12–6:13</a></p>\n<h3>As an image of something insubstantial</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl1:14\">ECC 1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:26\">JOB 6:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:29\">PRO 11:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:15-Prov27:16\">PRO 27:15–27:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:18\">ISA 26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:13\">JER 5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:1\">HOS 12:1</a></p>",
